title: CMU Neural Nets for NLP 2017 (6): Recurrent Neural Networks
description:
This lecture (by Graham Neubig) for CMU CS 11-747, Neural Networks for NLP (Fall 2017) covers:

* Recurrent Networks
* Vanishing Gradient and LSTMs
* Strengths and Weaknesses of Recurrence in Sentence Modeling
* Pre-training for RNNs

Slides: http://phontron.com/class/nn4nlp2017/assets/slides/nn4nlp-06-rnn.pdf
Code Examples: https://github.com/neubig/nn4nlp2017-code/tree/master/06-rnn

Previous Video: https://youtu.be/vnzKAhs7nds
Next Video: https://youtu.be/7j20MC6J_QU

See more details of the class here: http://phontron.com/class/nn4nlp2017/
